examples.korean: You should write about how you came to this country and how life is different in your home country. 발음듣기 어떻게 이곳에 오게 되었고 고향에서의 삶과 어떻게 다른지 쓰셔야 합니다. YBM All in All English-Korean Dictionary

examples.korean: They also wanted to see if the answers were different for each country. 발음듣기 그들은 또한 그 답들이 각 나라에 있어서 다른지를 알고 싶었다. Neungyule
examples.english: They also wanted to see if the answers were different for each country. 발음

examples.korean: Now let’s look at two pictures and talk about how they feel different. 발음듣기 이제 두 그림을 보면서 어떻게 느낌이 다른지 이야기해 봐요. YBM All in All English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: Now let’s look at two pictures and talk about how they feel different. 발음

examples.korean: Studying abroad is a wonderful way to make contacts in other countries and to understand how foreign economies and politics are different from your own. 발음듣기 해외 유학은, 다른 나라에서 사람들을 사귀고(문화를 접하고), 외국의 경제와 정책이 우리와 어떻게 다른지를 알 수 있는 아주 좋은 방법이다. Neungyule
examples.english: Studying abroad is a wonderful way to make contacts in other countries and to understand how foreign economies and politics are different from your own. 발음

examples.korean: Pyongyang, for instance, could explain about the exact locations of the submarines in question and how its torpedoes are different from the one Seoul presented as evidence. 발음듣기 예를 들면 북한은 공격에 사용되었을 것으로 추정되는 잠수함의 정확한 위치를 공개하며, 보유하고 있는 어뢰가 남한 측이 증거로 내놓은 것과 어떻게 다른지 설명할 수 있어야 한다. Neungyule
examples.english: Pyongyang, for instance, could explain about the exact locations of the submarines in question and how its torpedoes are different from the one Seoul presented as evidence. 발음
